o shape our politics and societies. Bringing French and francophone Belgian films into dialogue with carefully selected theories, O’Shaughnessy develops insights and an analytical framework that will become important resources for other scholars of contemporary cinema. This book explores cinema's capacity to register mutations in subjectivity, the material grounds for identity construction and the machinic dimension of neoliberal subjection. It also probes its capacity to imagine alternative economies and identities and an exit from neoliberal labour. By developing fresh insights into political cinema, this book provides engages with cinema’s response to neoliberalism in crisis.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGlobal Financial Crisis, 2008-2009, in motion pictures. 0aMotion pictureszBelgium. 0aMotion pictureszFrance. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2022z9783110992809oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2022 Englishz978311099281608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107803900 cprintz978147444862840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781474448642?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474448642423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474448642/original  a978-3-11-078039-0  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099281-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 